                     <interp inst="t18310407-279-person1927" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Peerless-row. The prisoner came to my house on the 16th of February, and borrowed a pair of morocco graining-plates for Mr. Knock - I let him have them; these are them.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q.Did you not say you gave me the plates? A. Yes, I gave them into your hand, as you stood at the door, for your master.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. You did not intend to part with the property? A.Certainly not, only to lend them to his master - he had borrowed them for him before.</p>
               <p>
            
